@startuml
title E6-01 — Propose and Approve Debt Transaction\nBusiness Control Map

top to bottom direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam nodesep 85
skinparam ranksep 95
skinparam padding 18

skinparam rectangle {
  FontSize 14
  MinimumWidth 250
}

rectangle "Draft Transaction" as Draft

rectangle "CONTROL 1\n\nDATA QUALITY AND ELIGIBILITY\n\nRequired fields\nProduct rules\nDate validation\nReference data\nTransaction limits" as Control1

rectangle "Validated Transaction" as Validated

rectangle "CONTROL 2\n\nSUBMISSION INTEGRITY\n\nValid status required\nSubmitted version created\nTerms locked for review\nSubmitter recorded\nTimestamp recorded" as Control2

rectangle "Submitted Transaction" as Submitted

rectangle "CONTROL 3\n\nAPPROVAL GOVERNANCE\n\nAuthorized approver\nApproval authority limits\nSegregation of duties\nComplete review package\nReturn reason required" as Control3

rectangle "Approval Decision\n\nApprove or return?" as Decision

rectangle "CONTROL 4\n\nRECORD AND AUDIT INTEGRITY\n\nDecision retained\nVersion history retained\nStatus updated\nParticipants notified\nApproved terms protected" as Control4

rectangle "Approved Transaction" as Approved

rectangle "Ready for\nSecurity Preparation" as Ready

Draft --> Control1
Control1 --> Validated

Validated --> Control2
Control2 --> Submitted

Submitted --> Control3
Control3 --> Decision

Decision --> Control4 : Approve
Control4 --> Approved

Approved --> Ready

Decision --> Draft : Return for revision

note right of Control1
Prevents incomplete,
ineligible, or internally
inconsistent transactions.
end note

note right of Control2
Creates a controlled
snapshot for approval.
end note

note right of Control3
Prevents unauthorized
approval and conflicts
between proposal and approval.
end note

note right of Control4
Preserves evidence of
what was approved,
by whom, and when.
end note

legend bottom
|= Control point |= Primary purpose |
| Control 1 | Ensure transaction data is complete and eligible |
| Control 2 | Protect the submitted version |
| Control 3 | Enforce approval authority and segregation of duties |
| Control 4 | Preserve the decision and audit evidence |

Each control should trace to:
• Business rules
• Acceptance criteria
• Test cases
• Audit evidence
endlegend

@enduml